claims:
Claims 1. A feeder unit for pigs comprising an elongate trough having a base and a sidewall for receiving and containing feed and arranged such that the head of the animal can reach over an upper front edge of the sidewall to the base for eating the feed, a hopper mounted over the trough for depositing feed downwardly; a feed dispensing control system at a bottom of the hopper so as to supply feed downwardly to make up feed taken by the pigs; said hopper including four upstanding side walls connected side edge to side edge to form a container for the feed material having a rectangular open top edge; an open upper guide mouth above the top edge for locating a downspout of a feed supply system through which feed is supplied to the hopper; said hopper including two opposed planar inclined walls each extending along a top edge of a respective one of the side walls and extending upwardly and inwardly of the side wall of the hopper to a position at the open upper guide mouth; each inclined wall having a lower horizontal edge equal in length to the top edge of the respective side wall and an upper horizontal edge at the guide mouth. 2. The feeder unit according to claim 1 wherein the guide mouth comprises a circular opening into which the downspout can be inserted. 3. The feeder unit according to claim 1 or 2 wherein the guide mouth comprises a hole in a rectangular plate into which the downspout can be inserted. 4. The feeder unit according to any preceding claim wherein the hopper is elongate with two long top edges and two short top edges and wherein said two inclined walls each extending upwardly from a respective long top edge. 5. The feeder unit according to claim 4 wherein the two short top edges are open or openable so that there is no fixed inclined wall at the short top edge. 6. The feeder unit according to claim 5 wherein the height of the guide mouth from the top edge and the spacing of the guide mouth from the short top edge is arranged such that when filled to the guide mouth the natural roposc angle of the feed prevents escape of the feed over the open top of the short top edges. 7. The feeder unit according to any preceding claim wherein the guide mouth is located at a height above that which can be accessed by the pigs. 8. The feeder unit according to any preceding claim wherein at least one of said inclined walls includes at least one location at which the wall can be opened to define an opening separate from the guide mouth through which a second downspout can be inserted. 9. The feeder unit according to claim 8 wherein said inclined wall includes two side by side openings separate from the guide mouth through two side by side downspouts can be inserted. 10. The feeder unit according to any preceding claim wherein there is provided at least one openable cover plate separate from the inclined walls covering parts of the top which are not covered by inclined walls. 1 1. The feeder unit according to any preceding claim wherein the hopper is elongate with two long top edges and two short top edges and wherein said two inclined walls each extend upwardly from a respective long top edge and wherein there is provided two openable cover plates each of which extends from a position at the guide mouth to a respective one of the short top edges. 12. The feeder unit according to claim 10 wherein said at least one openable cover plate is movable by a worker for inspecting feed inside the hopper and for accessing an adjustment mechanism inside at least one of the short sides. 13. The feeder unit according to claim 10, 1 1 or 12 wherein the openable cover plates are hinged at the top at the guide mouth. 14. The feeder unit according to claim 13 wherein the hinged cover plates are hinged across a transverse line so as to fold inwardly and allow movement of a bottom edge of the hinged cover plate inwardly. 15. The feeder unit according to claim 14 wherein the hinged cover plates are arranged to be latched at a raised open position. 16. The feeder unit according to claim 13, 14 or 15 wherein the hinged cover plates include downturned side edges which extend over a side edge of the inclined walls to prevent penetration of water between the edge of the cover plate and the edge of the inclined wall. 17. The feeder unit according to claim 13, 14 or 15 wherein the hinged cover plates include a top flange portion which extends over a horizontal top plate containing the open mouth to prevent penetration of water between the flange portion of the cover plate and horizontal top plate. 18. The feeder unit or method according to any preceding claim wherein the feed dispensing control system comprises an elongate shelf which extends substantially along a full length of the trough and provides a substantially horizontal surface for receiving feed, said horizontal surface of said shelf being arranged at a height above and rearwardly of said front edge and separate from said trough such that any feed falling therefrom along the full length thereof can fall directly vertically downwardly into the trough and so as to allow access by the head of the animal to said shelf for direct feeding therefrom, and between said shelf and said front edge to said base. 19. The feeder unit or method according to claim 18 wherein there is provided a water supply underneath the shelf operable by the pigs. 20. A feeder unit for pigs comprising an elongate trough having a base and a sidewall for receiving and containing feed and arranged such that the head of the animal can reach over an upper front edge of the sidewall to the base for eating the feed, a hopper mounted over the trough for depositing feed downwardly; a feed dispensing control system at a bottom of the hopper so as to supply feed downwardly to make up feed taken by the pigs; 

 said hopper including four upstanding side walls connected side edge to side edge to form a container for the feed material having a rectangular open top edge; an open upper guide mouth above the top edge for locating a downspout of a feed supply system through which feed is supplied to the hopper; said hopper including two opposed inclined walls each extending along a top edge of a respective one of the side walls and extending upwardly and inwardly of the side wall of the hopper to a position at the open upper guide mouth; wherein the hopper is elongate with two long top edges and two short top edges; wherein said two inclined walls each extend upwardly from a respective long top edge; and wherein there is provided two openable cover plates each of which extends from a position at the guide mouth to a respective one of the short top edges. 21. A feeder unit for pigs comprising an elongate trough having a base and a sidewall for receiving and containing feed and arranged such that the head of the animal can reach over an upper front edge of the sidewall to the base for eating the feed, a hopper mounted over the trough for depositing feed downwardly; a feed dispensing control system at a bottom of the hopper so as to supply feed downwardly to make up feed taken by the pigs; 

 said hopper including four upstanding side walls connected side edge to side edge to form a container for the feed material having a rectangular open top edge; an open upper guide mouth above the top edge for locating a downspout of a feed supply system through which feed is supplied to the hopper; said hopper including two opposed inclined walls each extending along a top edge of a respective one of the side walls and extending upwardly and inwardly of the side wall of the hopper to a position at the open upper guide mouth; wherein the hopper is elongate with two long top edges and two short top edges; and wherein the height of the guide mouth from the top edge and the spacing of the guide mouth from the short top edge is arranged such that when filled to the guide mouth the natural repose angle of the feed prevents escape of the feed over an open top of the short top edges.
